[Command]
	- wraps up actions inside an object so you can run them at a later time.
		ex) delay one action, delay many, or even set a specific time for them to happen.

		ex) add executables into a list and use for-loop to execute each.

	- Advantage
		-> ability to undo commands.
			+ Returning to the previous state
			+ Computing deltas
			+ Defining opposite operations

	* In Android, Use case execute as a form of the Command pattern is appropriate and aligns well with modern Android development practices.
